name: Semma
description:
A deeply personal tribute
              to the chef Vijay Kumar’s upbringing in the South Indian state of Tamil Nadu and home to the city’s best
              dosa. Ranked No. 1 on The Times’s 2025 list of best New York City restaurants.

name: ATOMIX
description:
Tasting menu restaurant
              known for its punchy, distinctly Korean flavors, understated service and use of modern presentation and
              techniques. Ranked No. 2 on The Times’s 2025 list of best New York City restaurants.

name: Le Bernardin
description:
Elegant, airy Midtown
              institution specializing in ambitious seafood dishes. Known for attracting a well-heeled crowd and service
              that is charmingly French. Ranked No. 3 on The Times’s 2025 list of best New York City restaurants.

name: Kabawa
description:
The first stand-alone
              restaurant from the chef Paul Carmichael, a Barbados native and longtime Momofuku chef. Expect exuberant,
              richly spiced Caribbean cuisine made with care and served with palpable joy. Ranked No. 4 on The Times’s
              2025 list of best New York City restaurants.

name: Ha's Snack Bar
description:
The first brick-and-mortar
              space for a longtime pop-up restaurant where dishes inspired by Vietnamese, French and other cuisines come
              together in creative and striking ways. Ranked No. 5 on The Times’s 2025 list of best New York City
              restaurants.

name: King
description:
Beloved, nearly decade-old
              restaurant that’s kept true to its owners’ original vision: Open a deeply personal, Southern French- and
              Italian-accented restaurant on a sunny corner in the West Village with a seasonal menu. Ranked No. 6 on
              The Times’s 2025 list of best New York City restaurants.

name: Penny
description:
East Village seafood
              counter known for dishes that are beguiling in their simplicity and cunning in their execution. Ranked No.
              7 on The Times’s 2025 list of best New York City restaurants.

name: Sushi Sho
description:
Tucked-away omakase
              restaurant from the renowned sushi chef Keiji Nakazawa, where he shows the transformative power of his
              ingredients. Ranked No. 8 on The Times’s 2025 list of best New York City restaurants.

name: Mountain House Flushing 川山甲
description:
Queens location of a
              popular and influential Chinese restaurant specializing in dishes from the Sichuan region. Ranked No. 9 on
              The Times’s 2025 list of best New York City restaurants.

name: Tatiana by Kwame Onwuachi
description:
The chef Kwame Onwuachi’s
              ode to the Afro-Caribbean culinary diaspora and New York City food culture. Ranked No. 10 on The Times’s
              2025 list of best New York City restaurants.

name: 188 Bakery Cuchifritos
description:
Bronx "pork palace" known
              for its pernil and cuajitos among other pork-centric specialties from Puerto Rico and the Dominican
              Republic.

name: A&A Bake Doubles and Roti
description:
Bedford-Stuyvesant
              restaurant specializing in doubles — chewy, stretchy bara bursting at the seams with mildly sweet and
              warmly spiced chana.

name: Abuqir
description:
Longtime Egyptian haunt
              known for its choose-your-own-adventure approach to whole fish and other well-executed Middle Eastern
              dishes.

name: Aska
description:
Scandinavian restaurant
              from the chef Fredrik Berselius, known for inventive cooking and a vibrant tasting menu that manages to be
              playful, soulful and entirely fresh.

name: Atoboy
description:
Eclectic
              Korean-influenced restaurant serving a $75 prix-fixe menu featuring dishes like kimchi with beurre blanc
              and buchu muchim with chimichurri.

name: Bar Jamon
description:
Bar arm of Casa Mono
              featuring aged Cava, musky vintage Rioja and other deep cuts, as well as a full menu.

name: Barbuto
description:
Beloved Manhattan
              institution from the chef Jonathan Waxman, a Chez Panisse alum. Known for its unimprovable roast chicken
              with a salsa verde made with herbs, capers and anchovies.

name: Barney Greengrass
description:
Iconic Upper West Side
              delicatessen and appetizing shop specializing in smoked fish, matzo ball soup and other Jewish
              staples.

name: Birria-Landia
description:
First location of the
              popular food truck that put Tijuana-style birria on the map in New York City.

name: Birria-Landia NYC
description:
Manhattan location of the
              popular food truck that put Tijuana-style birria on the map in New York City.

name: Birria-Landia
description:
Brooklyn location of the
              popular food truck that put Tijuana-style birria on the map in New York City.

name: Birria Landia
description:
Bronx location of the
              popular food truck that put Tijuana-style birria on the map in New York City.

name: Borgo
description:
The first Manhattan
              restaurant from the Brooklyn restaurateur Andrew Tarlow, featuring a trattoria-style menu that changes
              seasonally.

name: Bridges
description:
Stylish Chinatown hot
              spot from an Estela alum offering an imaginative, globally inspired menu amid chic, minimalist
              decor.

name: Bungalow
description:
East Village restaurant
              from the celebrity chef Vikas Khanna showcasing regional Indian cuisine.

name: Cafe Kestrel
description:
Unfussy and cozy jewel
              box of a restaurant in Red Hook with a focus on European and New American cuisine.

name: Cafe Mado
description:
Laid-back all-day cafe
              serving breakfast and lunch, as well as a refined and ambitious dinner menu in the former Oxalis
              space.

name: Carnitas Ramirez
description:
Pork-focused taqueria,
              inspired by Mexico City, from the couple behind Taqueria Ramírez in Greenpoint.

name: Casa Mono
description:
Andy Nusser's
              longstanding restaurant dedicated to bold Spanish flavors and nose-to-tail cooking. Home to an expansive
              wine list featuring aged Cava, musky vintage Rioja and more.

name: Cervo's
description:
Dimes Square restaurant
              featuring a menu of bright, olive-oil-soaked seafood inspired by the Iberian Peninsula, with olives and
              anchovies aplenty.

name: Chambers
description:
Low-key restaurant and
              bar with an 89-page wine list, curated by the celebrated sommelier Pascaline Lepeltier, and
              Greenmarket-driven plates from a Gramercy Tavern vet.

name: Chez Ma Tante
description:
Greenpoint restaurant
              famous for its butter-soaked pancakes and gutsy, Euro-Canadian sensibility, a nod to Montreal.

name: Cho Dang Gol
description:
Koreatown institution
              with a focus on homemade tofu served in varying states of wobbly, as well as Korean classics like pajeon
              and bibimbap.

name: Chongqing Lao Zao 重慶老灶
description:
Flushing hot pot fixture
              with a dizzying assortment of accouterments and a simple but delicious dessert menu.

name: Çka Ka Qëllu
description:
A rustic tavern decorated
              with Albanian artifacts, and a focus on the culinary riches of Albania and Kosovo, serving a vast spread
              of meats and dips.

name: Çka Ka Qëllue
description:
Manhattan location of the
              Bronx-born restaurant with a focus on the culinary riches of Albania and Kosovo, serving a vast spread of
              meats and dips.

name: Claud
description:
Sophisticated wine bar
              with an intelligently quirky, classically schooled kitchen from a Momofuku vet.

name: Cocina Consuelo
description:
Harlem restaurant with a
              homey atmosphere and menu of dishes inspired by a childhood spent in Puebla and Oaxaca.

name: Court Street Grocers
description:
Original location of a
              mini-chain specializing in an eclectic menu of fat, inhalable sandwiches.

name: Court Street Grocers Williamsburg
description:
Local mini-chain
              specializing in an eclectic menu of fat, inhalable sandwiches.

name: Court Street Grocers
description:
Local mini-chain
              specializing in an eclectic menu of fat, inhalable sandwiches.

name: Crown Shy
description:
Seasonal restaurant from
              the chef James Kent located on the ground floor of an Art Deco landmark building in the financial
              district.

name: Daniel
description:
Three-decade-old classic
              French restaurant from the famed chef and restaurateur Daniel Boulud.

name: Dera Restaurant
description:
Traditional Pakistani
              food (all halal) served in a large cafeteria-like setting in the Jackson Heights neighborhood.

name: Dhamaka
description:
Lower East Side
              restaurant from the team behind Semma, specializing in lesser-known regional cuisines of India.

name: Don Peppe
description:
Decades-old red-sauce
              Italian restaurant teeming with racetrack memorabilia.

name: Ewe's Delicious Treats
description:
Tiny Brooklyn restaurant
              serving deeply flavored and complex Nigerian and West African dishes.

name: Eyval
description:
Hip Bushwick restaurant
              from a former Sofreh chef serving dishes inspired by Iranian street food.

name: The Four Horsemen
description:
Williamsburg hot spot
              with a seasonally minded menu and expansive natural wine list.

name: Four Twenty Five, a Jean-Georges Restaurant
description:
Upscale fine dining
              restaurant helmed by the chefs Jean-Georges Vongerichten and Jonathan Benno.

name: Frenchette
description:
Modern brasserie from the
              team behind Le Rock and Le Veau d'Or.

name: Gage & Tollner
description:
Revival of a 19th-century
              restaurant, serving steakhouse fare, raw seafood and elaborate desserts.

name: Golden Diner
description:
Downtown hot spot with
              cheffed-up takes on diner classics like pancakes and patty melts.

name: Gramercy Tavern
description:
Service-minded Flatiron
              institution with a seasonally minded menu.

name: Great NY Noodletown
description:
Chinatown favorite with
              an encyclopedic menu and a diverse, all-ages crowd.

name: THE GRILL
description:
Luxe steakhouse and
              restaurant from the Carbone team in the former home of the Four Seasons.

name: Hainan Chicken House | 海南鸡记
description:
Sunset Park restaurant
              specializing in Malaysian Hainanese chicken rice perfumed with jasmine, pandan, lemongrass and
              shallots.

name: Hamburger America
description:
Counter specializing in
              Oklahoma onion burgers from the burger-obsessed chef George Motz.

name: Hellbender
description:
Casual bar and restaurant
              serving soulful, ingredient-driven Mexican American cooking in an increasingly hip corner of
              Queens.

name: Hindu Temple Canteen
description:
Basement cafeteria
              beneath a Queens Hindu temple serving dosa, idli, vada and other South Indian dishes.

name: Ho Foods
description:
Taiwanese standby for
              crisp-edged radish cakes, fan tuan, invigorating housemade soy milk and soul-warming beef noodle
              soup

name: Houseman
description:
Homey,
              expectation-busting neighborhood restaurant serving a New American menu.

name: Jean-Georges
description:
Elegant tasting menu
              French restaurant overlooking Central Park since 1997.

name: Jeju Noodle Bar
description:
West Village destination
              for impeccably fresh seafood and pristine bowls of Korean ramyun.

name: Jungsik
description:
Fine-dining, tasting-menu
              restaurant serving a refined selection of inventive Korean dishes.

name: Keens Steakhouse
description:
More than century-old,
              wood-paneled steakhouse known for mutton chops and classic fare.

name: Kisa
description:
Hip Korean restaurant
              serving baek ban platters in the style of the taxi stand restaurants of South Korea.

name: Koloman
description:
French and Austrian fine
              dining restaurant on the ground floor of the Ace Hotel.

name: Kono
description:
Refined dining counter
              serving yakitori skewers in the style of omakase.

name: Kopitiam
description:
All-day cafe serving
              Nyonya cuisine, a blend of Chinese and Malaysian food traditions.

name: Laghman Express
description:
Modest Bensonhurst
              storefront offering dishes from Uzbek, Kazakh, Tajik and Uyghur cuisines, including hand-pulled noodles
              with cumin lamb.

name: Lakruwana Restaurant
description:
Sri Lankan restaurant
              adorned with dozens of artifacts collected over the years by the Wijesinghe family and known for its
              popular weekend buffet.

name: Le Coucou
description:
Pricey French restaurant
              helmed by an American chef who used to cook in Paris and seamlessly blends Gallic traditions with downtown
              swagger.

name: Le Veau d'Or
description:
The second coming of a
              beloved French bistro from the team behind Frenchette and Le Rock.

name: Levant
description:
Steinway Street gem
              specializing in feteer — flaky, layered bread — among other Egyptian delights.

name: Lilia
description:
Missy Robbins's temple to
              handmade pasta and other Italian specialities.

name: Little Myanmar
description:
Family-run restaurant
              showcasing the breadth of Burmese cuisines, including oxtails, samosas and noodle dishes.

name: Lola's
description:
NoMad restaurant serving
              a low-key but inspired menu of seasonal dishes served in an unfussy, convivial dining room.

name: Lucia Pizza Of Avenue X
description:
Contemporary pizza
              restaurant with a reverence for the old from a second-generation pizzaiolo.

name: Mắm
description:
Tiny restaurant serving
              baskets of grilled intestines, sticky-rice sausage and more, alongside potent condiments, to customers
              seated at colorful plastic stools on Forsyth Street.

name: Mountain House - Times Square 川山甲
description:
Midtown location of a
              popular and influential Chinese restaurant specializing in dishes from the Sichuan region. Ranked No. 9 on
              The Times’s 2025 list of best New York City restaurants.

name: Mountain House
description:
East Village location of
              a popular and influential Chinese restaurant specializing in dishes from the Sichuan region. Ranked No. 9
              on The Times’s 2025 list of best New York City restaurants.

name: OKDONGSIK New York
description:
13-seat counter serving
              dweji gomtang, a pork-based variation on Korean gomtang, and mandu.

name: Okiboru House of Tsukemen
description:
Lower East Side
              destination for tsukemen and tontori ramen, with a vegetarian option.

name: OldSportFood
description:
Queens restaurant
              specializing in Lanzhou beef noodle soup from northwestern China with thin noodles, refreshing broth and
              chile crisp.

name: Raf's
description:
Stylish low-lit French
              Italian restaurant powered by a wood-fired oven in a former bakery space.

name: Raku
description:
East Village location of
              a popular mini-chain of restaurants specializing in Japanese udon afloat in complex, deeply flavored
              dashi.

name: Raku
description:
Greenwich Village
              location of a popular mini-chain of restaurants specializing in Japanese udon afloat in complex, deeply
              flavored dashi.

name: Raku
description:
Midtown location of a
              popular mini-chain of restaurants specializing in Japanese udon afloat in complex, deeply flavored
              dashi.

name: Randazzo's Clam Bar
description:
Decades-old Sheepshead
              Bay clam bar best known for its fried calamari and other Italian American seafood dishes.

name: S&P Lunch
description:
Recently revived lunch
              counter from the team behind Court Street Grocers in the space once occupied by Eisenberg's Sandwich
              Shop.

name: Sailor
description:
Trendy seasonal
              restaurant on a popular dining strip in Fort Greene.

name: Salty Lunch Lady's Little Luncheonette
description:
Corner Ridgewood cafe
              known for lovingly made sandwiches and a rotating dessert menu.

name: Shaw-nae’s House
description:
Staten Island soul food
              and American restaurant in a homey space.

name: Shukette
description:
Ayesha Nurdjaja's modern
              Middle Eastern restaurant with a wide-ranging, deftly executed menu.

name: Sofreh
description:
Prospect Heights
              restaurant located just off a busy Brooklyn thoroughfare specializing in Persian cuisine with a homemade
              feel.

name: Superiority Burger
description:
Second iteration of
              Brooks Headley's popular vegetarian and vegan restaurant in the former home of a Ukrainian diner.

name: Sushi Noz
description:
Upper East Side omakase
              counter from the Japanese chef Nozomu Abe serving pristine, high-end sushi.

name: Sushi Ouji
description:
SoHo restaurant serving
              a carefully curated 14-course menu of otsumami, nigiri and futomaki, all for a quarter of the price of the
              more expensive places.

name: Taiwanese Gourmet
description:
Cash-only, no-nonsense
              oasis of Taiwanese cooking operating in Elmhurst since the 1990s.

name: Thai Diner
description:
Popular downtown spot
              for Thai American food from the team behind the now-closed Uncle Boons.

name: Third Falcon
description:
Cozy Fort Greene
              restaurant with a concise, seasonal menu from an Eleven Madison Park alum.

name: Torrisi
description:
Stylish reincarnation of
              the groundbreaking restaurant that put the chef Rich Torrisi and Major Food Group on the map.

name: Trinciti Roti Shop & Restaurant
description:
JFK-adjacent restaurant
              known for its doubles, aloo pie, curry goat and other Trinidadian specialties.

name: Txikito
description:
Insider-y Chelsea
              restaurant specializing in food from the Basque region of Spain.

name: Una Pizza Napoletana
description:
Anthony Mangieri's
              temple to Neapolitan-style pizzas, open just three days a week.

name: Via Carota
description:
Breezy West Village
              restaurant with celebrity clientele and a focus on seasonal Italian cuisine.

name: Village Cafe
description:
South Brooklyn
              destination for plov (Azerbaijani rice pilaf) and other dishes.

name: White Bear
description:
Walk-up window for
              affordable bites, including pork wontons with chile oil.

name: Yoon Haeundae Galbi
description:
Korean barbecue
              restaurant best known for its “Haeundae cut” short rib.

name: ZAAB ZAAB
description:
Original location of a
              mini-chain of restaurants serving fiery Isan-style Thai cooking with a focus on seafood.

name: Zaab Zaab
description:
Brooklyn location of a
              mini-chain of restaurants serving fiery Isan-style Thai cooking with a focus on seafood.

name: Zaab Zaab
description:
Manhattan location of a
              mini-chain of restaurants serving fiery Isan-style Thai cooking with a focus on seafood.
